mpest\n|\nLoving yourself costs nothing, but not loving yourself could cost you everything.\n\n- B.D. Jordan, A Calling Dream\n|\nAfter a dream like that, you're grateful that it was just a dream, that no matter how bad your actual life, it couldn't be worse than your dream life.\n\n- Brock Clarke, An Arsonist's Guide to Writers' Homes in New England\n|\nAs we go, we become more deeply committed to a life of purpose and meaning and personal decency as we come to feel a broader connection to the shared experience of humanity.\n\n- Auliq-Ice\n|\nDo not despise your own place and hour. Every place is under the stars, every place is the center of the world.\n\n- John Burroughs, Studies in Nature and Literature"